Field & data Managementofficer
Posted :30 April, 2014
1,625 views
Experience: 3 to 4 yearsJob Location: Quetta
Department / Job Category: Others
Last Date: 11 May, 2014
Main Duties & Responsibilities:
To collect the data from DPMs about their field activities such as PHWs, LHWs and CAHWs, for their awareness and other outreach activities with purpose of zoonoses prevention and control.
To do follow-up of  established Union Council Coordination Committees (UCCC) in Pishin and Zhob districts for their monthly meeting and their role in zoonoses prevention and control.
To strengthen the coordination among UCCCs and ZCC for disease surveillance, reporting and response in the two districts
To facilitate and support ZCCs in implementing its action plans in the districts.
To develop success stories about diseases surveillance and reporting mechanism.
To enter field data and generate reports on the base of process data.
To assist program team in data entry and processing
To share the field visits reports to APMs.
To share bi-weekly and monthly progress report regarding ZCC, UCCCs of Pishin & Zhob  and data entry of all target districts.
Qualifications:
Having Master Degree .
Must have knowledge of the health safety and Zoonotic diseases prevalent in the area.
At least 3-4 years of progressive experience and proven track record of relevant competence of working with NGOs/INGOs.
Experience of working in unstable or conflict affected areas and willingness to work in very remote areas with limited services and amenities.
Must be able to work independently and together with the project team.
Having adept knowledge of computer applications and soft wares (MS Word, MS Excel & Power point).
Strong leadership, communication, and Interpersonal skills.
